               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) ʾO-ʾǝgziʾǝyä ʾIyasus Krǝstos ʿǝqäbänni ... “Oh My Lord Jesus Christ, protect me ...” (litanical prayer to Christ) (fols. 4r-19r) (s. S.GRÉBAUT, “La prière ‘ʿƎqäbänni’ ou les litanies du Christ”, Orientalia nuova ser. 4, 1935, 426-40)&#xD;
II) ʾAstäbqwǝʿot ʾǝntä za-Sǝmʿon ʿamdawi “Prayers of Simeon Stylite” (fols. 19r-74v) (s. P.LEANDER, "ʾAstabqueʿōt ʾǝnta za-Semʿōn ʿamdāwī, nach Handschriften in Uppsala und Berlin herausgegeben", Le Monde Oriental 11, 1917, 81-130)&#xD;
III) Malkǝʾ-hymn to St Mary (fols. 74v-81v, 1r-3r) (ascribed to <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> Giyorgis of Gāsǝč̣č̣ā) (s. ChRep 196, no. 91).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I contains the embedded colophon (<locus target="18v">18v</locus>) which states that the book was translated from a Western/Occidental language and that Gabra Krǝstos was the translator:</note>
                     <note>… ተርጎምክዋ፡ ለዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ አነ፡ ገብረ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ እምነገረ፡ አፍርንጊ፡ ኀበ፡ ነገረ፡ ኢትዮጵያ፡</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text III is ascribed to <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> Giyorgis of Gāsǝč̣č̣ā. The traditional title is Ṣalot za-ʾabba Giyorgis “Prayer of <roleName type="title">ʾabbā</roleName> Giyorgis”. The text is included in Maṣḥafa gǝbra ḥǝmāmāt “Book of the Rite of the Holy Week” (s. Ethiopian Orthodox Church (ed.), Gǝbra ḥǝmāmāt, Addis Abäba 1942 A.M. [1949/50 A.D.], repr. 1972 A.M. [1979/50],<ref type="mss" corresp="ES471477">471-477</ref>). The beginning section of the prayer, ዘሌሊት (za-lelit, “for the night hours”), is missing. Here, the text has been interrupted on the last fol. because of the lack of space, the rest having been added on the fly-leaves.</note>
                  </msItem>
